            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-23T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-23T05:00:00-05:00" n="1500" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363/6–2349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-23T18:00:00+08:00">June 23, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 23—6:50 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2448. Re ConGentel 2442, June 23, 5 p. m. Workers who invaded StanVac building
                    have rejected bonus proposal and company offer to negotiate further with Labor
                    Bureau as mediator. Five foreign executives including Coltman caught in building
                    have barricaded selves in offices. Workers in corridors gradually adopting more
                    threatening attitude. No sign police intend to intervene. Inform StanVac
                    Washington representative of both messages for relay New York.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
